-- Goldman Sachs has a 2.1 pct stake in Italy's Banco Popolare
-- By Elisa Anzolin
-- Mon Mar 17, 2014 10:29AM EDT
-- None



MILAN, March 17 (Reuters) - U.S. bank Goldman Sachs <GS.N> has a 2.116 percent stake in Italian cooperative lender Banco Popolare <BAPO.MI>, according to a filing posted on market watchdog Consob's website on Monday.

Investors in listed Italian companies have to notify the watchdog when their holding exceeds 2 percent.